# `.spec`

This folder is the package-local Spec Led layer.

<!-- spec.workspace.readme_present -->

## Canonical Layout

- `README.md` (authored)
- `AGENTS.md` (authored, local operating guidance for agents working in this folder)
- `decisions/README.md` (authored ADR guidance for this workspace)
- `decisions/*.md` (authored durable cross-cutting ADRs)
- `specs/spec_system.spec.md` (authored, meta-spec for this folder)
- `specs/package.spec.md` (authored, package-level intent)
- `specs/*.spec.md` (authored subject specs)
- `state.json` (generated by `mix spec.plan` and `mix spec.verify`)

## Core Loop

1. make the smallest code, docs, or test change that moves the behavior
2. add or tighten the smallest proof when behavior changed
3. run `mix spec.assist`
4. if it says `needs subject updates`, update the right current-truth subject in `specs/`
5. if it says `needs decision update`, add or revise an ADR only when the change is cross-cutting and durable
6. when it says `ready for check`, run `mix spec.check`
7. run `mix spec.diffcheck` when you need diff-aware enforcement
